Riverside Drive, at the N.E. corner of West 114th Street, showing the Althea Rudd Ward home. This structure, more than 100 years old, is to be razed and replaced with a 12 story apartment building according to a newspaper clipping dated Jan. 5, 1911.

1894

title: Columbia Court. North Corner Riverside Drive and 115th Street.

text:
North (Hudson) River, shore and skyline, Manhattan, at the foot of West 116th Street, showing Columbia University's boathouse at that point. Buildings seen across the Park are on the east side of Riverside Drive, from West 115th (right) to 117th Streets.

August 31, 1926.

P. L. Sperr.
title: North (Hudson) River - Shore and skyline - Manhattan - 59th Street - George Washington Bridge - [Columbia University Boat Club.]
